editorialSummary.text: Straightforward Greek cuisine such as seafood & lamb served in warm digs with exposed-wood beams.

originalText.text:
What an excellent meal!  The service was outstanding and the vibe is excellent.

If you are hungry for home style Greek food, this is seriously the spot for you.

Greek salad, zucchini chips, and tzatziki...no brainer to start. Add a mixed grill...and you are golden. The lamb chops are unbelievable!  Throw in a couple Fix beers to wash down the delicious fries.

Overall, super authentic and great service = wow!

originalText.text:
Come and share the zucchini fries and enjoy the vibes. That’s all I would go for imo.

The vibes were cool. Good hang out spot. But food was mid. Lamb chops, meat platter and lemon potatoes were all underwhelming, especially for the price. There’s much better Greek style food elsewhere.

originalText.text:
The best Greek food I have ever had in my life. All the dishes are delicious. The service are amazing. Staff is very nice and friendly.

It is pretty crowded both lunch and dinner. I am not sure they take a reservation since I walked in twice from my visit.

Zuchhini cheese is the best. Crispy and cheese but so yummy. The best ever.
The greek salad is amazing.
Grilled Octopus one is also my favorite as well.
Grilled Cheese on sear pan also nice.

originalText.text:
Food overall was ok. Zucchini fries were actually really good and calamari was a pretty good deal. Mains weren't great. Braised lamb didn't have too much flavour and no side. Chicken portion was generous but not that tasty.

Pretty cramped space and not worth waiting in line for tbh. Don't really understand the hype besides the cheap wine.

originalText.text:
Terrible dining experience. Unfriendly to Asian customers.

I found someone wrote a similar comment a week ago, and ours is worse.

The reception arranged three of us at a single square table very crowded. I asked to switch to a larger one but they claimed there is no room, despite I saw an empty booth. And had to wait at least 15-20 minutes to order. The waiter responsible for that table then challenged us that why we sit there, and I just told him that I was brought here.

While me and my family were sharing the Lamb Frikasse Delicate, the waiter suddenly appeared and took away the plates without ask. I argued with him after a while but he refused to replenish the sauce for us.

He sent another waitress to claimed that if we need sauce I would have to re-order the whole dish.

I paid in cash to get discount but the waiter kept the discount change, and he even threw the rest of changes back on table

I will never return. Unrecommended. The restaurant is overrated.
